post_text:
Dear Parents and Guardians,

Attached is a letter to help clarify and answer some of the questions we have recently received after sending out the mandatory re-entry form. Included in the letter are some of the main components of our district's plan (that’s still in draft form/tentative) as of today. Our re-entry plan will be sent to all after the state deadline on Wednesday, July 29. We are required to align our plan with the State Department of Education, and it will not be radically different from their recommendations. We appreciate your patience and assistance in effectively planning for full re-entry and distance learning based on the recommendations from Governor Lamont, Commissioner Cardona, and our local health department.

The health and safety of all students is our highest priority. Thank you for your patience and understanding during this time when protocols/recommendations are continuously changing.

Sincerely,
Marco Gaylord

post_text: Every 10 years, the @uscensusbureau undertakes a mammoth task: counting all the people residing in the United States. This count affects the allocation of funding for our community’s public resources (e.g., roads, hospitals, schools), how we plan for the future, and our voice in government. Learn more about the importance of the #2020Census and how to participate: 2020census.gov.

Health Equity Solutions
May 6, 2019 at 5:37 PM ·

Are you African-American or Latino/Latina/Latinx and live in Middlesex County? Then we want to hear from you!!!

HES has been contracted to do focus groups on health and well-being in Middlesex County for the Middlesex county NAACP. The information will inform planning efforts to address health and well-being in the County.

post_text:
The Champions Zero Suicide Committee at Rushford has teamed up with the American Foundation for Suicide Prevention for the Out of the Darkness campus walk. Every year suicide claims more lives than war, murder, and natural disasters combined. Together we can change the conversation about mental health and put a stop to this tragic loss of life.



The walk will take place on Saturday, June 16 from 9am-12pm here at WWMS. We want to have as many walkers there as we can. Here is the link to the website to register, please cut and paste: www.afsp.org/middletown Please feel free to share. Anyone can walk. Donations are accepted, but they are not required. The flyer for the event is attached.

Thank you for your support!

post_text:
At MHS we have a three-course program in Early Childhood Development with a co-curricular, hands on preschool program - "Blue Dragon Preschool".

The main focus is learning about child development. The highlight of the program is a preschool program featuring our high school students working with a children ages 3-5. Ten preschool aged children are chosen each year. High school students create and implement lesson plans for each session of preschool, which meets three times per week. This year marks the 10th anniversary of the Blue Dragons Preschool Program!
